# Copy to ``app/.env`` and set your Mac’s hostname (Bonjour / mDNS ``*.local``).
# Works from iOS Simulator, a phone on the same Wi‑Fi, and this machine—no separate LAN IP needed.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# Example (replace with your machine’s Bonjour name from Sharing settings):
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://helios.local:8000/api/v1
#
# Purely on this Mac (no physical device): ``http://localhost:8000/api/v1`` is fine.
# API must accept LAN traffic: Docker maps ``8000:8000`` by default; bare ``uvicorn`` needs ``--host 0.0.0.0``.
